ools/intelmq/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">644</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":644,\"repo\":\"certtools/intelmq\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - IntelMQ is a solution for CERTs for collecting and processing security feeds, pastebins, tweets using a message queue protocol. It's a community driven initiative called IHAP (Incident Handling Automation Project) which was conceptually designed by European CERTs during several InfoSec events. Its main goal is to give to incident responders an easy way to collect &#x26; process threat intelligence thus improving the incident handling processes of CERTs. <a href=\"https://www.enisa.europa.eu/activities/cert/support/incident-handling-automation\">ENSIA Homepage</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-09-14T06:41:02.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1442188800000,"to":1442275199999,"previousId":"2015-09-15","nextId":"2015-09-13","nextName":"Sep 13th, 2015","previousName":"Sep 15th, 2015"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","4035379035"]}